parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to premature wear, damage, or even engine failure, which can result in costly repairs or leave the driver stranded.

Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to move, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or strand the driver. In some cases, the vehicle may roll uncontrollably if parked on an incline, posing a significant safety risk.
symptoms: the crankshaft position sensor is damaged.
